results.occurrenceRemarks: Feb. 10: Sometime in the afternoon I looked through my kitchen window and saw in my back yard, along my wooded border, a black squirrel with an orange tail that scampered rather quickly out of sight. I discovered online that it wasn't a hybrid but instead a melanistic color phase of the Eastern Gray Squirrel. I have many gray squirrels (and an occasional red squirrel and chipmunk) in the winter around my bird feeders, but this is the first time I have ever viewed a black/orange squirrel mix (reportedly rare) as well as the first such sighting in the 40+ years I have lived on this property. Feb. 11: At 9 AM EST I spotted the same squirrel again in my back woods. Once more it was on the move, never stopping long enough for me to snap a decent pic.
